== Subtraction - ==

Subtraction is a binary operation. It should not be confused with [/wiki/peano/arithmetic/negative-sign | the negative sign].
For natural numbers the [/wiki/peano/arithmetic/half-minus | the half minus] operator is used which does not go below
0.

=== Definition ===

Subtraction is defined using [/wiki/peano/arithmetic/negative-sign | the negative sign] as
#(= (- a b) (+ a (-n b))) /edit/peano_new/arithmetic/common/negative.gh/df-minus#.

=== Properties ===

* Cancellation: #(= (- a a) (0)) /edit/peano_new/arithmetic/common/negative.gh/minuscan#
* Identity:  #(= (- a (0)) a) /edit/peano_new/arithmetic/common/negative.gh/minusid#

